cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with digital camera pipelines and color constancy methods. The use of learning-based methods also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. The aggregation of data from different camera sensors and diverse scene content could also suggest that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of color temperature grouping could suggest that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
